        },
        "$:/plugins/tesseract/forloop/Readme": {
            "text": "!!! __''Purpose''__

Provides a simple for-loop, which replaces specified word with iterated values. 

!!! __''Parameters''__



|!Parameter |!Description |
|text |The string/text to be processed [Mandatory] |
|forvar |The variable in the string that should be replaced with the value of for loop. |
|initval |The initial value to be assigned to the looping variable [Defaults to 0]|
|maxval |The cut-off value of the loop [Defaults to 10]|
|iter |The number by which looping variable should iterate [Defaults to 1] |
|joiner|The string/symbol/html-entity that should separate the iteration of loop. [Defaults to `<br/>`]|


!!! __''Usage''__

```
<$macrocall $name=for
text="Hello world myvar"
forvar=myvar
initval=5
maxval=100
iter=5
/>
```

Outputs

<$macrocall
$name=for
text="Hello world myvar"
forvar=myvar
initval=5
maxval=100
iter=5
/>

TIP: You can use transclusion or helper macros to assign the text. for eg `text={{Hello There}}` or `text=<<mytextmacro>>`

While it is not mandatory, it is a recommended practice to wrap  the variable with $, for eg: $myvar$ -for readability purposes. ",
